{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/339/comments/36338162.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/sdformat/diff/osrf/sdformat:12529e265fd8..e52c48cc0820?path=include%2Fsdf%2FFilesystem.hh"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/339/_/diff#comment-36338162"}}, "parent": {"id": 36336879, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/339/comments/36336879.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/339/_/diff#comment-36336879"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 339, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/339.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/339"}}, "title": "Remove boost 16"}, "content": {"raw": "I didn't realize this is a `void *`. I don't think you can declare a `void` `unique_ptr`, although I believe is possible with a `shared_ptr` but in this case the semantics of a `shared_ptr` and the overhead are not a good fit. I'd leave it as it is. (You could do the reinterpret_casts by using the `.get()` function).", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I didn't realize this is a <code>void *</code>. I don't think you can declare a <code>void</code> <code>unique_ptr</code>, although I believe is possible with a <code>shared_ptr</code> but in this case the semantics of a <code>shared_ptr</code> and the overhead are not a good fit. I'd leave it as it is. (You could do the reinterpret_casts by using the <code>.get()</code> function).</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-05-05T18:03:13.256592+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Carlos Ag\u00fcero", "uuid": "{da8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bda8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bda8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/692bf15758111acaddae4d